        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles south of Audra State Park to near Rock
Cave. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Buckhannon, Mill Creek, Dailey, Holly River State Park, Rock Cave,
Beverly, Womelsdorf (Coalton), Huttonsville, Alexander, Eden,
Helvetia, Pickens, Cleveland, Alton, Walkersville, Hacker Valley,
Ellamore, Kanawha Head, Ireland, and Tallmansville.

This includes Route 33 between mile markers 15 and 31.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
